Lifemate Group has announced that it will introduce electronic appliance brand, Vimate. A statement from the company yesterday said Vimate is a new merchandising enterprise that incorporates electrical products display, operations and customer service. ‘’In 2018, Vimate was set up in the world’s second largest economy, China, and registered in Nigeria early 2019, thereby starting the process of officially entering the electrical appliance chain industry. Vimate is an incubation and enjoys the empowerment of well-known Lifemate Group, which has given rise to the inevitable outcome of Vimate’s rapid development’’, the statement said. The company said Vimate which is set to launch this month in Abuja will create a one-stop shopping mall where anything and everything about a home can be purchased, all in one place. Lifemate rewards customer with N1.5m Lifemate begins sofa swap promo Modern shopping centres take over Ibadan Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.